The Bayero University Kano will on Saturday, June 15, confer an Honorary Doctor of Business degree on the Chairman of UBA Group and founder, Tony Elumelu Foundation, Mr. Tony O. Elumelu. The honour, the university said, is in “recognition of his innumerable and worthy contributions to the country as an economist, entrepreneur, and philanthropist”. According to the vice chancellor of the university, Elumelu’s “philanthropic activities through the Tony Elumelu Foundation (TEF) have reached every nook and cranny of our nation and have impacted positively on many lives.” His “efforts in the area of entrepreneurship are making immense contributions to the economy,” he added. Tony Elumelu Foundation (TEF) is Africa’s foremost champion of entrepreneurship on the continent. It was founded in 2010 by Tony O. Elumelu, an entrepreneur, investor and philanthropist who is passionate about Africa’s economic development. The Tony Elumelu Foundation Entrepreneurship Programme is a $100 million commitment by the Elumelu family to empower 10,000 African entrepreneurs over a 10-year period across the 54 countries of the continent. He serves as the chairman of UBA Group, now present in 20 African countries, Paris, London and New York, and the only African bank with a deposit taking presence in the United States. He is the founder and chairman of Heirs Holdings, a family-owned investment company, committed to improving lives and transforming Africa. Macron for 2000 TEF entrepreneurs in Lagos Elumelu Foundation opens application for $100m African entrepreneurs grant Elumelu Foundation to assemble 5,000 entrepreneurs Oct Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin